column1: Table 9: Land area and population density by administrative area, mid-2018

1) 2018 Council areas and 2018 NHS Board areas. The 2018 areas differ from the previous 2011 Council areas and 2014 NHS Board areas due to a small boundary change at Keltybridge (which did not affect the population), between Fife and Tayside.

2) Land areas were derived from Standard Area Measurements produced by the Office for National Statistics and include geography changes up until 31 December 2017. A small boundary change at Keltybridge was introduced in early 2018, however this change involved minimal land movement and is unlikely to affect any density calculations. Figures may not add exactly because of rounding.
3) Persons per square kilometre has been calculated using actual, not rounded areas.
